						<div class="postbody">Hi all,
<br />
<br />Now that I have a few NROM devcarts, I want to try to make some basic demos that I can run on my NES.
<br />
<br />I don't know much about the 6502, but I recently purchased the book by Zaks that was mentioned in another thread. I must also admit that I don't know much about programming, but I am very willing to learn. I'm not looking for "try something easier first" or "this isn't for beginners". When I started the devcart stuff a few months ago, I never touched a soldering iron before. I'm not saying I'm a genius, but I think I pick up things rather quickly.
<br />
<br />I've messed around with editors, and have understand sprites, tiles, and other basic information. I want to try to make a simple demo - with a background and one sprite that I can move around the screen.
<br />
<br />I'm sure I went about this the wrong way - but I tried NBasic, and was able to make what I described above - but it only runs in what must be fairly inaccurate emulators. The ASM that NBasic spits out is pretty confusing - the code I see around here makes a bit more sense. I can post the Nbasic / ASM code if anyone wants to take a look. Perhaps the ASM can be cleaned up to run on other emulators, maybe even my NES.
<br />
<br />What I'm hoping for is some example code some of you may use in your programming - hopefully I can make sense of it as I continue to read and experiment. I would also like to compare it to the ASM spit out by NBasic. Also, if anyone has any simple demos like I'm trying for with source code available - that would be nice.
<br />
<br />If you read this far, thanks..
<br />
<br />NC</div>

