				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">First of all, you should stop using Nbasic. You need to fully understand the 6502 assembly language if you plan to make a game. Or anything that will run on the NES at all. I suggest to first learn the 6502. I know, just like I did, you probably hate hearing that sentence, don't you? I did too. But when I snapped out of being lazy for a moment, I learned the 6502, and it is quite a simple language to understand. 
<br />
<br />I really don't want to show you how to make a moving sprite with a background right now, if you don't understand the 6502. It's like learning a different language(like spanish, japanese, etc., not like C/C++) , If I just taught you sentences, and not the structure or the vocabulary, you wouldn't learn anything (My spanish teacher teaches us alot of sentences as apposed to sentence structure, and it pisses me off!). Same thing here. If I were to just teach you how to do certain things with the NES, you'd never learn. You must learn the sentence structure and vocab. You'll then be able to come up with the sentence on your own. Understand?</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.freewebs.com/the_bott/" class="postlink">-Owner of Poultry Games</a></div>
