						<div class="postbody">You do have a point there, but we aren't dealing with small children learning their first language. I meant it like learning a second language. When learning a second language, you know what's going on, and how to speak, unlike when learning your first language. When learning a second language, you want to learn the way the language works, the vocabulary, then put sentences together. And also, you're not a small child who doesn't know that there are seperate words in a sentence or what a sentence is period.</div>

					
