						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Celius wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">First of all, you should stop using Nbasic.</div><br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">No Carrier wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I'm sure I went about this the wrong way - but I tried NBasic,</div><br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">Celius wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You need to fully understand the 6502 assembly language if you plan to make a game.</div><br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">No Carrier wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What I'm hoping for is some example code some of you may use in your programming - hopefully I can make sense of it as I continue to <strong>read and experiment.</strong></div><br /><br />I am learning, slowly. I just wanted to see some other's code. Oh, and I never said anything about making a game. Just a simple demo.<br /> <br /><div class="quotetitle">Celius wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I really don't want to show you how to make a moving sprite with a background right now, if you don't understand the 6502.</div><br /><br />Wonderful. Please don't be offended, but then why did you waste your time posting two paragraphs of useless information? If you didn't intend to help, maybe you shouldn't have posted. I'm sorry your Spanish teacher pisses you off, but did you ever think that others may learn in a different way than you?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">Celius wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Understand?</div><br /><br />Yep. Maybe I shouldn't be replying in this fashion to someone who was <strong>trying</strong> to help, but I'm surprised that you responded in this manner. I've seen enough of your rambling, whining, inane posts.. and I figured you'd help a fellow newbie out.<br /><br />Remember posting this?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">Celius wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">This isn't an emulation question, but I ask it here, because people only seem to be active here. But, I'm not sure 